- - - ( PHP Custom Router ) - - - 


A single point of entry (usually index.php) 
  â†’ every request goes through this file

Inside it, you write logic that maps a URL (or route) 
  to some handler/controller/function



* ("Code"):


<?php

require 'functions.php'; 
//Contains a function that returns a boolean if a filepath is matched

 
$uri = parse_url($_SERVER['REQUEST_URI'])['path'];
//Parses the URL, limiting the path returned w/o query strings 

 
$routes = [
 '/' => 'controllers/index.php'
 '/about'  => 'controllers/about.php'
 '/contact' => 'controllers/contact.php'
] 
//Assoc_Array which Contains Key( path ) & Value( page )


function Abort(){
 http_response_code(404);
 echo "No Such Content Available";
 die();
}
// A Function which... Returns a 404 Status, and "die" / ends execution ( in summary "Abort" )


if ( array_key_exists(*Key, *Assoc_Array) ){ require $routers[$uri];}
else{ Abort(); }
//Checks if the given name of the Key, within the Assoc array exists
//If condition met, it now "require" the page( value ) of the Corresponding Key
//Else calling the "Abort function"

?>


